`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The `mineRock` amount formula uses `Math.floor(rngValue * (range + 1))` clamped to `maxAmount`. This gives a uniform distribution over `[minAmount, maxAmount]` inclusive when `rngValue ∈ [0, 1)`. At `rngValue = 0.99`, `Math.floor(0.99 * 3) = 2` for a range of 2 — which maps correctly to `maxAmount`. The `+ 1` in `range + 1` is the same trick used in standard dice-roll math.
